Love is in the air and we couldn't be more thrilled! This one in particular as I've known Yazmin since she was a little girl. So when I was asked to capture her surprise proposal I both excited and honored to be a part of it. Congratulations Yazmin & Matt! So happy for what the future holds for you

"Love knows no age, for every heart in love is young"
-
Photographing and getting to know Paul and Bonnie has been an absolute pleasure and highlight in my career. At ages 85 and 70+ respectively they are my oldest couple and can easily say one of my favorites
-
They both look amazing, were both wildly successful in their careers, and are absolutely inspiring just to be around
-
We're going to go big for their wedding and I couldn't be more thrilled to be the one capturing their memories. Stay tuned as I'm about to spam your feed with our wonderful engagement session

Needless to say it was a beautiful day with one of the most perfect sunsets I think I've ever seen out here. I loved being able to capture such a special time in Marjan & Rob's pregnancy. Thank you for choosing me as your photographer ♥️

Maternity is a time to celebrate the miracle of life. It is time to be grateful for the gift of motherhood and to look forward to the joy of meeting your new baby. If you're pregnant, cherish the special time as it's a time that you will never forget♥️

Beautiful setting for the start of a beautiful life together ❤️
- - -
Photo: @francisralphphoto 
Venue: @jfgsandiego

Family is a blessing and I love when I get to capture  such a special time in their lives. This is our second maternity session and I couldn't be more excited for them! Thank you Kayla & Christian for having me as your photographer. Love watching your family grow in front of my lens❤️

Amongst all this beauty what stands out the most is the love between Hali & Sam. I know I can see it. Can you?

Be sure and catch the full image in our stories to get the full magnitude of this shot before it's gone
As I look at this photo it gives me a sense of appreciation. Appreciation of small and quiet moments. Appreciation of the ocean. Appreciation of being with a loved one and just be❤️
Message to the baby...We haven't met you yet, but just know we all already love you❤️
Skyline kisses in Seattle❤️
A fitting ending to a beautiful engagement session in Seattle

We're counting down the days until we get to see Andrea & Bryan say "I do". I know it's going to be the most magical day of their lives thus far, and I can't wait to be there to witness/capture it all❤️

A rainbow is a symbol of hope, new beginnings and love. So to have a rainbow appear during Ayla & Steven's first kiss as husband and wife made for a truly magical moment and sign that their love was meant to be

The Queen Mary's very Regal Ballroom, otherwise known as the Queen's Salon. One of the most gorgeous spaces I've ever photographed a reception in. For more information please see @photosqueenmary comment below

I'm so excited to share that I had the pleasure of  photographing the engagement session of my long time friend Yazmin! I've known Yazmin since she was a child and it's amazing to watch her grow into the beautiful and confident woman she is today.

Yazmin's fiance Matt is as good of a guy as I think I've ever met and a perfect match for Yazmin.  They're both kind, funny, and loving and I can tell they're going to have a long and happy life together. 

I captured some truly magical moments between them and I can't wait to see what the future holds for these two!

Weddings are all about creating magical moments, and a bubble tunnel is the perfect way to do it! Imagine walking down the aisle surrounded by a sea of bubbles as your loved ones look on and wonder. It's a truly unforgettable experience!

Andrea and Bryan nailed this! Their bubble tunnel was one of the best I've ever seen.

With a little planning you can create a bubble tunnel that will be the talk of your wedding just like Andrea & Bryan

Weddings are meant to be magical, and there's no better place to say "I do" than @botanicathevenue. With its lush gardens and cascading waterfalls. It's the perfect setting for a truly unforgettable day.

Andrea and Brian chose to exchange vows in front of the waterfall and it was the perfect backdrop for the love. The water was rushing by, the sun was shining, and the birds were singing. It was truly a dream come true

To me beach love is the best love especially when it's two beautiful people like Yazmin & Matt. Throughout our shoot you could feel the carefree and romantic spirit of these two perfect for a beach engagement.

They laughed, they kissed, and they embraced all surrounded by the beauty of nature. I'm so excited for them to start this next chapter in their lives together!! Congratulations again Yazmin & Matt!!

Such class and grace shown by Jackie and Jen throughout the day. Their wedding didn't necessarily go as planned but they showed what matters most...not the details but the love between you and your partner. Congratulations Jackie and Jen!! I wish you a lifetime of happiness!!

The rain and cold of Seattle can create an atmosphere of mystery, drama, and tranquility. The skyline provides a unique backdrop for storytelling, while the chill in the air can evolve a sense of longing....

Yeah we were freezing!!! We literally did a big group hug between shots for warmth. Sure it was less than ideal conditions but did we have fun? Heck yeah!!

Kudos to Hali, Sam, and Tiffany for doing my crazy ideas! Full Image in Stories

Not gonna lie but I'm having a lot of fun doing holiday sessions. It's just so great watching the kids grow up in front of my camera

If you're still in need of that last minute portrait session. We have a limited number of slots left for individuals, couples, and families. Special Holiday Pricing still available. Book your session today and create lasting memories that you'll cherish for years to come!

I'm loving the Pacific Northwest more and more every time I'm out there! With the emerald greens, fiery oranges, and deep reds brought about by the rain,  the surrounding foliage painted a picturesque backdrop for Hannah & Matthew's special engagement session. This was a great day

I can't get over how perfect Volunteer Park was for Matthew & Hannah's engagement. Not only was it the place where Matthew proposed but the vibrant colors of all the leaves provided a stunning backdrop for their story.

Yes it rained and yes we had to race against the clock due to lighting, but we were all smiles as we explored the park's various trails and gardens. So excited to celebrate their wedding next year! Congratulations again Matthew & Hannah!!

Lost in love amidst the enchanting vines at @callawaywinery. Sipping on the sweetness of romance in every grape-filled moment. Cheers to Sara & Luis and to their love that only gets better with time!
